1
00:00:11,907 --> 00:00:14,241
[ Wind howling ]

2
00:00:15,876 --> 00:00:18,643
-You are Liz T. Blood.
Is that correct?

3
00:00:18,676 --> 00:00:19,976
-Yes.

4
00:00:20,009 --> 00:00:21,176
-Records show you departed
the Acropolis

5
00:00:21,209 --> 00:00:22,609
with your older brother.

6
00:00:22,643 --> 00:00:23,809
Is he not with you?

7
00:00:23,843 --> 00:00:25,643
-He went home ahead of me.

8
00:00:25,676 --> 00:00:27,943
-There's nothing in my file
that indicates he's returned.

9
00:00:27,976 --> 00:00:30,143
-Enough! I'm in a hurry!
Now let me pass!

10
00:00:30,176 --> 00:00:31,743
-Let her through.

11
00:00:31,776 --> 00:00:33,343
I'll handle this.

12
00:00:33,376 --> 00:00:35,043
-Officer Beros!

13
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:36,343
[ Pop! ]

14
00:00:36,376 --> 00:00:38,876
-Let's go.
I'll escort you to your mansion.

15
00:00:38,909 --> 00:00:40,176
-[ Clears throat ]
Excuse me.

16
00:00:40,209 --> 00:00:43,343
You've got a little gum
on your face.

17
00:01:00,209 --> 00:01:04,209
-[ Singing in Japanese ]

18
00:02:22,464 --> 00:02:25,397
-As I'm sure you're aware,
I'm with the Acropolis Police,

19
00:02:25,430 --> 00:02:27,464
and my job
is to maintain order here.

20
00:02:27,497 --> 00:02:28,797
-Hmm.

21
00:02:28,830 --> 00:02:30,297
-I've been wanting

22
00:02:30,330 --> 00:02:31,597
to speak with your brother
for a while now,

23
00:02:31,630 --> 00:02:33,564
but he somehow managed
to get past me.

24
00:02:33,597 --> 00:02:35,830
-He had some urgent business
to attend to, so he --

25
00:02:35,864 --> 00:02:39,530
-Coming and going without proper
authorization is a crime.

26
00:02:39,564 --> 00:02:43,030
So, that gives me the authority
to take him into custody

27
00:02:43,064 --> 00:02:45,897
by using
my special dispensation magic.

28
00:02:45,930 --> 00:02:47,830
-Where will you take him?

29
00:02:47,864 --> 00:02:51,364
-To the last person he'd ever
want to see in the Demon World.

30
00:02:51,397 --> 00:02:52,564
-You don't mean...

31
00:02:52,597 --> 00:02:54,064
-That's right.

32
00:02:54,097 --> 00:02:59,730
King of Demon World Acropolis,
Wolf-Daddy, himself.

33
00:02:59,764 --> 00:03:01,964
-Why would you force him
to see that jerk?

34
00:03:01,997 --> 00:03:03,930
-Watch your mouth.
That's our king.

35
00:03:03,964 --> 00:03:05,930
-What does he want
with my brother?

36
00:03:05,964 --> 00:03:08,397
-I'm not allowed
to disclose that information.

37
00:03:08,430 --> 00:03:09,964
It's all classified.

38
00:03:09,997 --> 00:03:13,630
-That guy's no king, not to us.

39
00:03:13,664 --> 00:03:15,864
He's the one who's responsible

40
00:03:15,897 --> 00:03:19,797
for taking mother and father
away from us forever.

41
00:03:21,764 --> 00:03:24,364
-There it is.

42
00:03:24,397 --> 00:03:25,630
[ Doorbell rings ]

43
00:03:25,664 --> 00:03:26,930
-Hmm?

44
00:03:26,964 --> 00:03:28,930
-Seems you have a visitor,
Santa Claus.

45
00:03:28,964 --> 00:03:32,664
-It appears so.
Excuse me for a moment.

46
00:03:32,697 --> 00:03:35,430
Do carry on with your work.
-[ Grumbles ]

47
00:03:35,464 --> 00:03:36,664
[ Door opens ]

48
00:03:36,697 --> 00:03:38,297
[ Doorbell rings ]

49
00:03:38,330 --> 00:03:39,764
-All right,
you four-eyed pervert!

50
00:03:39,797 --> 00:03:40,964
I know you're in there!

51
00:03:40,997 --> 00:03:42,697
You'd better come out now,

52
00:03:42,730 --> 00:03:44,764
or your sweet little sister's
gonna get it, understand?

53
00:03:44,797 --> 00:03:46,497
-I'm not your hostage!

54
00:03:46,530 --> 00:03:48,364
-Either you make him
come out here or get us inside!

55
00:03:48,397 --> 00:03:49,597
-Bite me!

56
00:03:49,630 --> 00:03:51,597
-My, my.

57
00:03:51,630 --> 00:03:53,830
Haven't changed a bit,
have you, Beros?

58
00:03:53,864 --> 00:03:55,997
To what do I owe
this great pleasure?

59
00:03:56,030 --> 00:03:57,664
-Stop playing games with me!

60
00:03:57,697 --> 00:03:59,764
Just shut your mouth
and open this damn gate now!

61
00:03:59,797 --> 00:04:00,997
-No, don't do it, brother!

62
00:04:01,030 --> 00:04:02,797
'Cause she's out here to --
[Muffled]

63
00:04:02,830 --> 00:04:04,697
-Hurry it up!

64
00:04:04,730 --> 00:04:08,330
-Of course.
Please come in, officer.

65
00:04:13,964 --> 00:04:18,530
-After hauling ass to get here,
I hope this is the right place.

66
00:04:20,397 --> 00:04:23,064
-Such nice color and aroma,
isn't it?

67
00:04:23,097 --> 00:04:25,764
I discovered
this wonderful herbal tea

68
00:04:25,797 --> 00:04:27,764
while visiting the lower world.

69
00:04:27,797 --> 00:04:30,797
-You entered
Demon World Acropolis illegally,

70
00:04:30,830 --> 00:04:32,530
and I'm here to arrest you.

71
00:04:32,564 --> 00:04:34,397
-Hmm.

72
00:04:34,430 --> 00:04:37,664
-I'm gonna wipe that smarmy look
right off of your face!

73
00:04:37,697 --> 00:04:40,630
Because my special dispensation,
the Underdog Choker,

74
00:04:40,664 --> 00:04:42,797
is gonna stick to you
wherever you go!

75
00:04:42,830 --> 00:04:46,064
-Underdog Choker!

76
00:04:46,097 --> 00:04:47,930
-[ Roaring ]

77
00:04:47,964 --> 00:04:49,630
-Hmm.

78
00:04:49,664 --> 00:04:51,997
-As long as that collar's
around your neck,

79
00:04:52,030 --> 00:04:54,830
you won't be able to use
any of your magic powers.

80
00:04:54,864 --> 00:04:57,597
And even if you try anything
funny, there'll be spilled blood

81
00:04:57,630 --> 00:05:00,530
mixed with that delicious
herbal tea you're drinking.

82
00:05:00,564 --> 00:05:02,797
-Interesting.

83
00:05:02,830 --> 00:05:05,897
This is your form of discipline,
is it?

84
00:05:05,930 --> 00:05:08,497
If you wanted to keep me
as your pet,

85
00:05:08,530 --> 00:05:10,530
you should have just said so.

86
00:05:10,564 --> 00:05:14,697
So, why don't you take me out
for a walk, then?

87
00:05:14,730 --> 00:05:16,297
-Brother?

88
00:05:16,330 --> 00:05:20,397
I'm really sorry
that I disobeyed your orders.

89
00:05:20,430 --> 00:05:22,397
-It's okay, Liz.

90
00:05:22,430 --> 00:05:24,697
I'm afraid
I'll be detained for a bit.

91
00:05:24,730 --> 00:05:27,064
[ Whispering ] You failed
to buy me some time,

92
00:05:27,097 --> 00:05:28,997
but will you
look after the house?

93
00:05:29,030 --> 00:05:31,630
-Mm-hmm.
-Thanks, Liz.

94
00:05:31,664 --> 00:05:34,030
You be a good girl, now.

95
00:05:36,330 --> 00:05:38,864
-Ohh.

96
00:05:40,864 --> 00:05:42,897
[ Cellphone rings ]

97
00:05:42,930 --> 00:05:45,297
-That you?
-Yeah.

98
00:05:45,330 --> 00:05:46,630
-Did you find Fuyumi?

99
00:05:46,664 --> 00:05:48,297
-[ Sniffles ] Not yet...

100
00:05:48,330 --> 00:05:49,497
-What's going on?

101
00:05:49,530 --> 00:05:50,797
Are you crying again?

102
00:05:50,830 --> 00:05:52,497
-Shut up!
I'm not crying!

103
00:05:52,530 --> 00:05:53,697
-You <i>are</i> crying.

104
00:05:53,730 --> 00:05:55,030
What's Braz doing?

105
00:05:55,064 --> 00:05:58,397
-He got in trouble
because of me and was...

106
00:05:58,430 --> 00:05:59,930
-What?!
He got arrested?!

107
00:05:59,964 --> 00:06:02,897
How we supposed to find Fuyumi
with Braz in custody?!

108
00:06:02,930 --> 00:06:05,064
- <i>I</i> can still look for her,
okay?

109
00:06:05,097 --> 00:06:06,864
It's just hard right now.

110
00:06:06,897 --> 00:06:09,797
'Cause she's stuck in a dark
place where I can't see her.

111
00:06:09,830 --> 00:06:11,797
-What?!
What are you talking about?!

112
00:06:11,830 --> 00:06:12,997
-'Sup, bitch!

113
00:06:13,030 --> 00:06:14,697
You ain't from around here, yo!

114
00:06:14,730 --> 00:06:16,797
So why you just
yappin' on the phone?!

115
00:06:16,830 --> 00:06:20,597
Woo, woo, woo, woo, woo, woo,
woo, woo, woo, woo, whaaat?!

116
00:06:20,630 --> 00:06:22,030
-Gotta go.

117
00:06:22,064 --> 00:06:23,597
Call me back the minute
you find anything out.

118
00:06:23,630 --> 00:06:25,297
-[ Sniffles ]
-And don't cry.

119
00:06:25,330 --> 00:06:26,897
You didn't
do anything wrong, okay?

120
00:06:26,930 --> 00:06:28,297
-Hey! I'm not crying!

121
00:06:28,330 --> 00:06:29,697
-Whatever.

122
00:06:29,730 --> 00:06:31,530
-Finally quit
that dumb-ass phone call, yo!

123
00:06:31,564 --> 00:06:33,830
I think you should
give <i>me</i> a ring, dude!

124
00:06:33,864 --> 00:06:35,297
"What's up, ya freak?"

125
00:06:35,330 --> 00:06:37,697
-Hey, have you ever seen
this guy before?

126
00:06:37,730 --> 00:06:38,897
I'm lookin' for him.

127
00:06:38,930 --> 00:06:40,297
-Huh?

128
00:06:40,330 --> 00:06:41,630
Yeah, I can't hear you, man!

129
00:06:41,664 --> 00:06:43,430
What's up, baby?

130
00:06:43,464 --> 00:06:44,597
[ Thud! Thud! Thud! ]

131
00:06:44,630 --> 00:06:46,897
Sorry! I've never seen him, sir!

132
00:06:46,930 --> 00:06:49,797
I regret that I couldn't
be of more assistance.

133
00:06:49,830 --> 00:06:51,397
-I see.

134
00:06:51,430 --> 00:06:53,564
-Oh! But the boss
might be able to hook you up!

135
00:06:53,597 --> 00:06:55,697
He, like, knows everything
for realz, my man!

136
00:06:55,730 --> 00:06:57,430
I'll take you to him, bro!

137
00:06:57,464 --> 00:06:59,397
-Fine.
I'll give it a shot.

138
00:06:59,430 --> 00:07:01,064
-Aw, hellz yeah!
Walk this way!

139
00:07:01,097 --> 00:07:03,830
-Just so we're clear, if I think
you're trying to set me up,

140
00:07:03,864 --> 00:07:06,497
I'll kill you.

141
00:07:06,530 --> 00:07:08,564
-Never mind!
Let's go <i>this</i> way!

142
00:07:12,897 --> 00:07:14,597
Hey, Yukki!
-It's freezing in here!

143
00:07:14,630 --> 00:07:16,397
-I got another customer
here for you!

144
00:07:16,430 --> 00:07:18,597
-Huh? Who's he?

145
00:07:18,630 --> 00:07:21,530
-Yeah, I thought the homeboy
could use a little help.

146
00:07:21,564 --> 00:07:23,564
So here he is all nice, right?
Mm-hmm!

147
00:07:23,597 --> 00:07:24,764
-Sure about that?

148
00:07:24,797 --> 00:07:26,397
-Come on, I can't take this!

149
00:07:26,430 --> 00:07:27,697
I'm freezing my ass off!

150
00:07:27,730 --> 00:07:28,897
-Sorry about that.

151
00:07:28,930 --> 00:07:30,630
I'm a snowman,

152
00:07:30,664 --> 00:07:32,997
so everything around me
starts to get kinda chilly.

153
00:07:33,030 --> 00:07:34,464
Sure is cold.

154
00:07:34,497 --> 00:07:35,564
-You're a snowman,
and you're cold?!

155
00:07:35,597 --> 00:07:36,797
-[ Laughs ]

156
00:07:36,830 --> 00:07:37,964
He's a boss man,
a comedian, or what?!

157
00:07:37,997 --> 00:07:39,730
-So why aren't you cold,
Fish Lips?

158
00:07:39,764 --> 00:07:41,897
-A snowman who gets too cold!
You're killin' me!

159
00:07:41,930 --> 00:07:44,930
-So, Sabao here tells me you're
looking for a little help.

160
00:07:44,964 --> 00:07:47,330
-Hey! Sabao's my name,
and awesome's my game!

161
00:07:47,364 --> 00:07:48,530
Pleased to -- Ooh!

162
00:07:48,564 --> 00:07:50,497
-I've been looking for this guy.

163
00:07:50,530 --> 00:07:51,697
-Hey, so, where you from?

164
00:07:51,730 --> 00:07:53,064
Yo, what's your name, anyway?

165
00:07:53,097 --> 00:07:54,730
-Does he look familiar?
-Hmm.

166
00:07:54,764 --> 00:07:55,830
-Hot pot time!

167
00:07:55,864 --> 00:07:57,397
That sounds great
right about now!

168
00:07:57,430 --> 00:07:59,464
Nothing beats a hot pot
in cold weather!

169
00:07:59,497 --> 00:08:00,697
And how about some Jjigae?

170
00:08:00,730 --> 00:08:03,630
Yeah!
Jjigae hot pot, baby!

171
00:08:03,664 --> 00:08:04,697
[ Crash! ]

172
00:08:04,730 --> 00:08:05,897
-Do you know him?

173
00:08:05,930 --> 00:08:07,630
-I've met him, yeah.

174
00:08:07,664 --> 00:08:10,797
Not sure where he is now,
but I know where he lives.

175
00:08:10,830 --> 00:08:12,530
Got his card right here.

176
00:08:12,564 --> 00:08:14,430
-Is it somewhere close by?!

177
00:08:14,464 --> 00:08:17,030
-I, uh, don't think
you'll be able to find him.

178
00:08:17,064 --> 00:08:18,697
-Huh?

179
00:08:18,730 --> 00:08:21,497
-He lives in
the Dimensional Highway,

180
00:08:21,530 --> 00:08:24,664
one of the seven wonders
of the Demon World.

181
00:08:24,697 --> 00:08:26,397
No one's ever traveled there.

182
00:08:26,430 --> 00:08:28,530
In fact,
it's never even been seen.

183
00:08:28,564 --> 00:08:32,030
-So you're saying that once this
guy's home, nothing can be done?

184
00:08:32,064 --> 00:08:33,430
He can't be followed?

185
00:08:33,464 --> 00:08:34,930
-That's right.

186
00:08:34,964 --> 00:08:37,730
There's a chance Knell
might still be around here.

187
00:08:37,764 --> 00:08:40,030
Take his business card.

188
00:08:40,064 --> 00:08:44,064
-He's a transporter.
He's got some strange powers.

189
00:08:44,097 --> 00:08:45,830
-I don't believe it.

190
00:08:45,864 --> 00:08:48,330
-Here's your compromise ramen!

191
00:08:48,364 --> 00:08:50,964
-[ Slurps ]

192
00:08:50,997 --> 00:08:52,364
Hmm?

193
00:08:52,397 --> 00:08:53,864
Oh, yeah.

194
00:08:53,897 --> 00:08:55,297
I guess I'd better
give her something to eat, too.

195
00:08:55,330 --> 00:08:57,030
Hey, can I get
another ramen over here?

196
00:08:57,064 --> 00:08:58,530
-Comin' right up!

197
00:08:58,564 --> 00:08:59,964
-'Kay, in the meantime,

198
00:08:59,997 --> 00:09:02,730
let's see how our guest
is doing in my Grid Room.

199
00:09:02,764 --> 00:09:06,930
Hope everything's fine
in there...Fuyumi.

200
00:09:06,964 --> 00:09:08,530
-Here you go!

201
00:09:08,564 --> 00:09:10,830
And I compromised
by giving you some extra eggs!

202
00:09:10,864 --> 00:09:12,364
-Thank you!
Presto!

203
00:09:12,397 --> 00:09:14,630
Now you see the bowl,
and now you don't.

204
00:09:14,664 --> 00:09:16,597
-Huh?

205
00:09:16,630 --> 00:09:17,897
-[ Screams ]

206
00:09:17,930 --> 00:09:20,430
-[ Chuckles ]
Pretty cool trick, huh?

207
00:09:20,464 --> 00:09:22,697
-You made
one of my bowls disappear!

208
00:09:22,730 --> 00:09:24,664
I ain't gonna compromise
on that one!

209
00:09:24,697 --> 00:09:26,997
You're gonna have
to pay for that bowl, got it?!

210
00:09:27,030 --> 00:09:28,397
-[ Chuckles nervously ]

211
00:09:28,430 --> 00:09:29,864
-And if you don't pay me
right now,

212
00:09:29,897 --> 00:09:31,997
then I'm gonna pick up the phone
and call the police!

213
00:09:32,030 --> 00:09:34,330
-Uh, okay, okay, fine.

214
00:09:34,364 --> 00:09:38,897
I'll get your bowl back for you.

215
00:09:38,930 --> 00:09:40,930
-What?! Hey, let go!
It's hot!

216
00:09:40,964 --> 00:09:42,664
You're spilling soup on me!

217
00:09:42,697 --> 00:09:44,630
If you won't let go,
then I'll just have to make you!

218
00:09:44,664 --> 00:09:45,764
Let go?!

219
00:09:45,797 --> 00:09:46,964
-Aah!

220
00:09:49,397 --> 00:09:50,530
[ Bell dings ]

221
00:09:50,564 --> 00:09:52,697
-[ Gasps ]

222
00:09:52,730 --> 00:09:55,364
What's with the bell?

223
00:09:56,830 --> 00:09:59,064
-[ Gasps ] Fuyumi!

224
00:09:59,097 --> 00:10:01,064
-What's up, puddin' pie?

225
00:10:01,097 --> 00:10:04,430
-Fuyumi just rang my bell.

226
00:10:05,397 --> 00:10:06,864
[ Gasps ]

227
00:10:06,897 --> 00:10:08,464
-What's the matter, now?

228
00:10:08,497 --> 00:10:10,897
-Hold on!
Why is <i>he</i> showing up?!

229
00:10:10,930 --> 00:10:13,497
-Girl, you had way too much
to drink last night.

230
00:10:13,530 --> 00:10:14,697
[ Cellphone rings ]

231
00:10:14,730 --> 00:10:15,964
-That you, Liz?

232
00:10:15,997 --> 00:10:18,664
-Staz!
I know where Fuyumi is!

233
00:10:18,697 --> 00:10:21,364
She's with some weird guy!
-Oh, yeah?

234
00:10:21,397 --> 00:10:24,964
Well, I just found out
who our kidnapper is.

235
00:10:24,997 --> 00:10:26,464
Where are they now?

236
00:10:26,497 --> 00:10:27,764
-Time to go!

237
00:10:27,797 --> 00:10:29,930
Pretty sure I just made
a big mistake.

238
00:10:38,330 --> 00:10:41,064
-Aww, shucks.
I thought I had you that time.

239
00:10:41,097 --> 00:10:42,530
-S-Sis?

240
00:10:42,564 --> 00:10:43,730
[ Ding! ]

241
00:10:43,764 --> 00:10:45,530
[ Distorted ] Aaaaaah!

242
00:10:45,564 --> 00:10:48,530
-Long time no see, Knell.

243
00:10:48,564 --> 00:10:51,864
[ Chuckles ]
You haven't changed a bit.

244
00:10:51,897 --> 00:10:55,664
-Back at ya, sis.
Thanks a lot.

245
00:10:58,445 --> 00:10:59,712
Ow!

246
00:10:59,745 --> 00:11:01,079
-All right.
Now tell me who hired you.

247
00:11:01,079 --> 00:11:03,879
'Cause I know all about
the cargo you're hauling around.

248
00:11:03,913 --> 00:11:05,313
[ Bell chimes ]

249
00:11:05,346 --> 00:11:07,646
Fuyumi happens to be
a friend of mine.

250
00:11:07,679 --> 00:11:10,213
I can't just stand by
and watch you take her away.

251
00:11:10,246 --> 00:11:12,646
-Great.
You <i>would</i> say this now.

252
00:11:12,679 --> 00:11:14,679
I tried e-mailing you about it.

253
00:11:14,713 --> 00:11:16,179
