00:20:05,346 --> 00:20:08,013
<i>This</i> is what you really
care about, isn't it?

494
00:20:08,046 --> 00:20:10,013
-If you read it, I'll shoot!

495
00:20:10,046 --> 00:20:11,979
-You already know
that's not gonna work.

496
00:20:12,013 --> 00:20:13,979
When are you gonna learn, Bell?

497
00:20:14,013 --> 00:20:16,713
-Aah!

498
00:20:16,746 --> 00:20:20,046
-Come on, why don't we sit down
and read this thing together?

499
00:20:20,079 --> 00:20:23,113
-I'm sorry, Staz.

500
00:20:23,146 --> 00:20:24,646
-Let's see now.

501
00:20:24,679 --> 00:20:26,879
"Number 163,
found Gourmet Flower"...

502
00:20:26,913 --> 00:20:29,113
-Okay! I'll say it!
I'll say it!

503
00:20:29,146 --> 00:20:31,013
You win! I give up!

504
00:20:31,046 --> 00:20:33,079
-Was that so hard?

505
00:20:36,746 --> 00:20:38,813
[ Gunfire ]

506
00:20:38,846 --> 00:20:40,813
-You just had to do that,
didn't you?!

507
00:20:40,846 --> 00:20:42,713
-Sorry!
Guess it slipped my mind.

508
00:20:42,746 --> 00:20:43,913
-You're disgusting!

509
00:20:43,946 --> 00:20:45,679
-By the way,
do I look all right?

510
00:20:45,713 --> 00:20:48,279
Hope I'm not so gross
that they can't show me on TV.

511
00:20:48,313 --> 00:20:53,146
I know this might be a bad time,
but you've got a nice ass.

512
00:20:53,179 --> 00:20:54,179
[ Gunshot ]

513
00:20:54,213 --> 00:20:56,279
-Feeling better?

514
00:20:56,313 --> 00:20:59,013
-Maybe you didn't see
how much blood I lost.

515
00:20:59,046 --> 00:21:01,279
Thanks for asking
<i>after</i> shooting me.

516
00:21:01,313 --> 00:21:05,079
-I don't understand you at all.

517
00:21:05,113 --> 00:21:06,279
<i>You're</i> the one who went crazy

518
00:21:06,313 --> 00:21:08,013
and wanted to start
a fight with me.

519
00:21:08,046 --> 00:21:09,779
Then, as soon
as I looked at your diary,

520
00:21:09,813 --> 00:21:10,979
you were ready to surrender.

521
00:21:11,013 --> 00:21:12,879
You're acting really weird.

522
00:21:12,913 --> 00:21:14,879
-It's all <i>your</i> fault, anyway.

523
00:21:14,913 --> 00:21:16,313
-Huh?

524
00:21:16,346 --> 00:21:18,113
-Ohh!
Just forget it, okay?!

525
00:21:18,146 --> 00:21:20,879
You wanna save your precious
Fuyumi, don't you?!

526
00:21:20,913 --> 00:21:22,313
Perfect! I'll help you out!

527
00:21:22,346 --> 00:21:25,179
I might as well, since I'm
nothing but a big loser!

528
00:21:25,213 --> 00:21:27,979
[ Thinking ] <i>It's not like</i>
<i>I really have a choice, do I?</i>

529
00:21:28,013 --> 00:21:30,046
<i>You're so desperate</i>
<i>to be around her all the time,</i>

530
00:21:30,079 --> 00:21:31,979
<i>trying so hard</i>

531
00:21:32,013 --> 00:21:33,979
<i>that you don't notice the</i>
<i>person right in front of you.</i>

532
00:21:34,013 --> 00:21:35,346
<i>What an idiot.</i>

533
00:21:35,379 --> 00:21:37,179
<i>You should try</i>
<i>and forget about Fuyumi.</i>

534
00:21:37,213 --> 00:21:39,979
<i>It's not like you can get her</i>
<i>back now, anyway.</i>

535
00:21:40,013 --> 00:21:42,179
<i>You don't even have enough</i>
<i>blood for yourself,</i>

536
00:21:42,213 --> 00:21:45,046
<i>but all you can think about</i>
<i>is giving it all to her,</i>

537
00:21:45,079 --> 00:21:48,279
<i>even though</i> I'm <i>the one who's</i>
<i>been here for you all along.</i>

538
00:21:48,313 --> 00:21:50,679
<i>If I opened my arms</i>
<i>and stood in the way,</i>

539
00:21:50,713 --> 00:21:52,879
<i>begging for you</i>
<i>to finally pay attention,</i>

540
00:21:52,913 --> 00:21:54,213
<i>you'd walk right through me.</i>

541
00:21:54,246 --> 00:21:55,879
<i>I'm such an idiot.</i>

542
00:21:55,913 --> 00:21:59,146
<i>What else can I say</i>
<i>except, "I give up"?</i>

543
00:22:01,713 --> 00:22:03,846
-I don't really understand it,
but I know it's my fault.

544
00:22:03,879 --> 00:22:05,246
-Huh?

545
00:22:05,279 --> 00:22:07,946
-I realize that no matter what,
I'm responsible.

546
00:22:07,979 --> 00:22:10,179
And, in the end,
it all comes back on me.

547
00:22:10,213 --> 00:22:14,113
So whatever you're upset about,
I'm sure it's something I did.

548
00:22:14,146 --> 00:22:17,646
And even if it isn't,
you can blame me, anyway, okay?

549
00:22:17,679 --> 00:22:19,879
-Just get to the point,
will you?

550
00:22:19,913 --> 00:22:22,079
-I've been thinking about this
for a long time,

551
00:22:22,113 --> 00:22:24,046
and I've finally
come to the conclusion

552
00:22:24,079 --> 00:22:25,979
that I'm more of a bad guy
than a hero.

553
00:22:26,013 --> 00:22:28,679
So if you're mad about
something, don't hide it.

554
00:22:28,713 --> 00:22:30,679
You can take it out on me.

555
00:22:30,713 --> 00:22:34,079
Just say, "It's all
your damn fault, Staz!"

556
00:22:34,113 --> 00:22:37,979
Just don't expect an apology
'cause I'm a bad guy.

557
00:22:38,013 --> 00:22:40,679
-Oh, come on.

558
00:22:40,713 --> 00:22:44,213
-What are you waiting for?
Do it.

559
00:22:47,538 --> 00:22:51,538
-[ Singing in Japanese ]

560
00:24:17,438 --> 00:24:18,605
-Fine, you're an ass.

561
00:24:18,638 --> 00:24:20,438
-Hey, I was just
trying to help ya!

562
00:24:20,471 --> 00:24:22,405
-I get it. I get it.
Thanks a bunch.

563
00:24:22,438 --> 00:24:24,205
[ Thinking ] <i>That was</i>
<i>a close call back there.</i>

564
00:24:24,238 --> 00:24:26,005
<i>I almost let him</i>
<i>find out everything.</i>

565
00:24:26,038 --> 00:24:29,205
<i>I have to hide my true</i>
<i>feelings, no matter what.</i>

566
00:24:29,238 --> 00:24:32,271
And, hey, this is all
<i>your</i> fault, dumbass!

567
00:24:33,738 --> 00:24:35,505
-Come on, boss!

568
00:24:35,538 --> 00:24:38,405
Can't you do anything about that
annoying jerk with the glasses?!

569
00:24:38,438 --> 00:24:40,038
-Patience, Officer Beros.

570
00:24:40,071 --> 00:24:41,705
Our orders from the king
are to bring him in alive.

571
00:24:41,738 --> 00:24:44,205
-I know, but I just want to kill
that four-eyed turd!

572
00:24:44,238 --> 00:24:46,538
-Next time on "Blood Lad,"
"Sins of the Eye Glasses."

573
00:24:46,571 --> 00:24:49,238
-In the Demon World,
it's good to be bad.

